      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "gRPC for GenAI APIs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "gRPC uses HTTP/2 as its transport and Protocol Buffers as its serialisation format. For GenAI backends that serve other services (mobile apps, microservices) rather than browsers directly, gRPC offers tighter schemas, smaller payloads, and first-class server-side streaming — making it well-suited for LLM token streaming between backend services."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The key constraint: browsers cannot call gRPC directly without a gRPC-Web proxy (e.g. Envoy or gRPC-Web for Node). If your primary client is a browser, REST/SSE is simpler. If your client is a mobile app, another microservice, or a CLI tool, gRPC's binary framing and schema enforcement are clear wins."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Architecture"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "gRPC GenAI server-side streaming architecture with Anthropic SDK"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Python gRPC server implements a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Chat",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " RPC that accepts a single "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ChatRequest",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and returns a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "stream of ChatChunk",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " messages — one per LLM token. Auth and rate-limiting attach as interceptors on the server side, equivalent to middleware in Express or FastAPI."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Protobuf Definition"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Define the service contract in a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ".proto",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " file. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "stream",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " keyword on the return type enables server-side streaming:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "protobuf"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "syntax = \"proto3\";\n\npackage chat;\n\nservice ChatService {\n  // Server-side streaming RPC: one request, many response chunks\n  rpc Chat (ChatRequest) returns (stream ChatChunk);\n\n  // Standard unary RPC for health checks\n  rpc HealthCheck (HealthRequest) returns (HealthResponse);\n}\n\nmessage Message {\n  string role    = 1;   // \"user\" | \"assistant\" | \"system\"\n  string content = 2;\n}\n\nmessage ChatRequest {\n  repeated Message messages = 1;\n  string model              = 2;\n  int32  max_tokens         = 3;\n  float  temperature        = 4;\n  string user_id            = 5;   // for rate limiting\n}\n\nmessage ChatChunk {\n  string delta = 1;    // text fragment\n  bool   done  = 2;    // true on the final chunk\n  string error = 3;    // set on error, empty otherwise\n}\n\nmessage HealthRequest {}\nmessage HealthResponse { bool healthy = 1; }"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Generate Python stubs from chat.proto\npython -m grpc_tools.protoc \\\n    -I proto/ \\\n    --python_out=src/generated/ \\\n    --grpc_python_out=src/generated/ \\\n    proto/chat.proto"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Python gRPC Server"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# src/server.py\nimport grpc\nimport anthropic\nfrom concurrent import futures\nfrom generated import chat_pb2, chat_pb2_grpc\nfrom config import settings\n\n_anthropic = anthropic.Anthropic(api_key=settings.anthropic_api_key)\n\nclass ChatServicer(chat_pb2_grpc.ChatServiceServicer):\n    def Chat(self, request: chat_pb2.ChatRequest, context: grpc.ServicerContext):\n        system_msg = next(\n            (m.content for m in request.messages if m.role == \"system\"),\n            \"You are a helpful assistant.\",\n        )\n        messages = [\n            {\"role\": m.role, \"content\": m.content}\n            for m in request.messages\n            if m.role != \"system\"\n        ]\n\n        try:\n            with _anthropic.messages.stream(\n                model=request.model or \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n                max_tokens=request.max_tokens or 1024,\n                temperature=request.temperature or 0.7,\n                system=system_msg,\n                messages=messages,\n            ) as stream:\n                for text in stream.text_stream:\n                    if context.is_active():\n                        yield chat_pb2.ChatChunk(delta=text, done=False)\n                yield chat_pb2.ChatChunk(delta=\"\", done=True)\n\n        except anthropic.APIError as e:\n            context.set_code(grpc.StatusCode.UNAVAILABLE)\n            context.set_details(f\"LLM error: {e}\")\n            yield chat_pb2.ChatChunk(error=str(e), done=True)\n\n    def HealthCheck(self, request, context):\n        return chat_pb2.HealthResponse(healthy=True)\n\ndef serve():\n    server = grpc.server(\n        futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=10),\n        interceptors=[AuthInterceptor(), RateLimitInterceptor()],\n    )\n    chat_pb2_grpc.add_ChatServiceServicer_to_server(ChatServicer(), server)\n    server.add_insecure_port(\"[::]:50051\")\n    server.start()\n    print(\"gRPC server listening on :50051\")\n    server.wait_for_termination()\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    serve()"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Server Interceptors (Auth and Rate Limiting)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Interceptors wrap every RPC call, equivalent to middleware in REST frameworks. Auth reads the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "authorization",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " metadata key:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# src/interceptors.py\nimport grpc, jwt, redis\nfrom config import settings\n\n_redis = redis.Redis.from_url(settings.redis_url)\n\nclass AuthInterceptor(grpc.ServerInterceptor):\n    def intercept_service(self, continuation, handler_call_details):\n        metadata = dict(handler_call_details.invocation_metadata)\n        token = metadata.get(\"authorization\", \"\").removeprefix(\"Bearer \")\n        if not token:\n            def abort(request, context):\n                context.abort(grpc.StatusCode.UNAUTHENTICATED, \"Missing token\")\n            return grpc.unary_unary_rpc_method_handler(abort)\n\n        try:\n            payload = jwt.decode(token, settings.jwt_secret, algorithms=[\"HS256\"])\n            # Attach user_id to trailing metadata — available in servicer via context\n            handler_call_details.invocation_metadata += (\n                (\"x-user-id\", payload[\"sub\"]),\n            )\n        except jwt.InvalidTokenError as e:\n            def abort(request, context):\n                context.abort(grpc.StatusCode.UNAUTHENTICATED, str(e))\n            return grpc.unary_unary_rpc_method_handler(abort)\n\n        return continuation(handler_call_details)\n\nclass RateLimitInterceptor(grpc.ServerInterceptor):\n    LIMIT = 20   # requests per 60-second window\n\n    def intercept_service(self, continuation, handler_call_details):\n        metadata = dict(handler_call_details.invocation_metadata)\n        user_id = metadata.get(\"x-user-id\", handler_call_details.client_address)\n        key = f\"grpc_rate:{user_id}\"\n\n        count = _redis.incr(key)\n        if count == 1:\n            _redis.expire(key, 60)\n        if count > self.LIMIT:\n            def abort(request, context):\n                context.abort(\n                    grpc.StatusCode.RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED,\n                    f\"Rate limit: {self.LIMIT} req/min\",\n                )\n            return grpc.unary_unary_rpc_method_handler(abort)\n\n        return continuation(handler_call_details)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Python gRPC Client"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The client calls the streaming RPC with a standard "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "for",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " loop — each iteration receives one "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ChatChunk",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " from the server:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# src/client.py\nimport grpc\nfrom generated import chat_pb2, chat_pb2_grpc\n\ndef chat(messages: list[dict], token: str) -> str:\n    channel = grpc.insecure_channel(\"localhost:50051\")\n    stub = chat_pb2_grpc.ChatServiceStub(channel)\n\n    request = chat_pb2.ChatRequest(\n        messages=[chat_pb2.Message(role=m[\"role\"], content=m[\"content\"])\n                  for m in messages],\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n    )\n    metadata = [(\"authorization\", f\"Bearer {token}\")]\n\n    full_response = \"\"\n    for chunk in stub.Chat(request, metadata=metadata):\n        if chunk.error:\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"LLM error: {chunk.error}\")\n        print(chunk.delta, end=\"\", flush=True)\n        full_response += chunk.delta\n        if chunk.done:\n            break\n\n    print()  # newline after streaming\n    return full_response\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    token = \"your-jwt-token\"\n    chat([{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Explain gRPC in one sentence.\"}], token)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Node.js gRPC Client"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For a Node.js service that calls the Python gRPC backend:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// src/grpcClient.ts\nimport * as grpc from \"@grpc/grpc-js\";\nimport * as protoLoader from \"@grpc/proto-loader\";\nimport path from \"path\";\n\nconst packageDef = protoLoader.loadSync(\n  path.join(__dirname, \"../../proto/chat.proto\"),\n  { keepCase: true, longs: String, enums: String, defaults: true }\n);\nconst proto = grpc.loadPackageDefinition(packageDef) as any;\n\nconst stub = new proto.chat.ChatService(\n  \"localhost:50051\",\n  grpc.credentials.createInsecure()\n);\n\nexport async function streamChat(\n  messages: Array<{ role: string; content: string }>,\n  token: string\n): Promise<string> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const metadata = new grpc.Metadata();\n    metadata.add(\"authorization\", \\`Bearer \\${token}\\`);\n\n    const call = stub.Chat(\n      { messages, model: \"claude-sonnet-4-6\", max_tokens: 1024 },\n      metadata\n    );\n\n    let fullText = \"\";\n    call.on(\"data\", (chunk: { delta: string; done: boolean; error: string }) => {\n      if (chunk.error) return reject(new Error(chunk.error));\n      process.stdout.write(chunk.delta);\n      fullText += chunk.delta;\n    });\n    call.on(\"end\", () => resolve(fullText));\n    call.on(\"error\", reject);\n  });\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TLS and mTLS for Production"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Production gRPC services should use TLS. For internal microservice-to-microservice calls, mutual TLS (mTLS) verifies both ends:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Server with TLS\nimport grpc\n\ndef serve_tls():\n    with open(\"certs/server.key\", \"rb\") as f:\n        private_key = f.read()\n    with open(\"certs/server.crt\", \"rb\") as f:\n        cert_chain = f.read()\n\n    credentials = grpc.ssl_server_credentials([(private_key, cert_chain)])\n    server = grpc.server(futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=10))\n    chat_pb2_grpc.add_ChatServiceServicer_to_server(ChatServicer(), server)\n    server.add_secure_port(\"[::]:50051\", credentials)\n    server.start()\n    server.wait_for_termination()\n\n# Client with TLS\ndef make_tls_channel() -> grpc.Channel:\n    with open(\"certs/ca.crt\", \"rb\") as f:\n        root_certs = f.read()\n    credentials = grpc.ssl_channel_credentials(root_certificates=root_certs)\n    return grpc.secure_channel(\"api.example.com:50051\", credentials)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "gRPC-Web for Browser Clients"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Browsers cannot call gRPC directly because they lack control over HTTP/2 trailers. Use gRPC-Web with an Envoy proxy:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# envoy.yaml — minimal gRPC-Web frontend config\nstatic_resources:\n  listeners:\n    - name: listener_0\n      address: { socket_address: { address: 0.0.0.0, port_value: 8080 } }\n      filter_chains:\n        - filters:\n            - name: envoy.filters.network.http_connection_manager\n              typed_config:\n                \"@type\": type.googleapis.com/envoy.extensions.filters.network.http_connection_manager.v3.HttpConnectionManager\n                codec_type: AUTO\n                route_config:\n                  virtual_hosts:\n                    - name: local_service\n                      domains: [\"*\"]\n                      routes:\n                        - match: { prefix: \"/\" }\n                          route:\n                            cluster: grpc_backend\n                            timeout: 300s\n                http_filters:\n                  - name: envoy.filters.http.grpc_web\n                  - name: envoy.filters.http.cors\n                  - name: envoy.filters.http.router\n  clusters:\n    - name: grpc_backend\n      connect_timeout: 0.25s\n      type: LOGICAL_DNS\n      http2_protocol_options: {}\n      load_assignment:\n        cluster_name: grpc_backend\n        endpoints:\n          - lb_endpoints:\n              - endpoint:\n                  address:\n                    socket_address: { address: grpc-server, port_value: 50051 }"
          }
        ]
      },
